cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the design of incentive mechanisms for caching in wireless device-to-device (D2D) networks. It involves the study of cost minimization problem for the base station (BS) and utility maximization problem for each user terminal (UT). This suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with wireless networks and D2D communication. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as it formulates the problem as a Stackelberg game. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the study of cost minimization and utility maximization. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the incentive mechanisms for content sharing among UTs. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves the design of a distributed caching scheme.
